<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by jgn77:
[I]1. Legend of Zelda/ LOZ 2 - Best ever in my opinion. Classic rpg.

2. Dragon Warrior 1,2,3,4 - First game I ever played that had levels, experience points, quests, available weapons/armor that got better as the game went on and a great story. 

3. Final Fantasy 3 (US) What a great game. Awesome story, Awesome gameplay, and awesome ending. 

4. Morrowind - This game glued me to the computer for 20 hours straight once. I mean I could not stop cause the list of quests are endless. Sure it has a few problems but if you can over look them, the game implants you into the role. I actually thought I was the hero instead of contoling the hero. 

5. Diablo 2 - Played the single player all the way through and loved it. Single player seemed to be a great challenge cause there was no one there to help you along. The multiplayer aspect of this game is the best ever. It's just plain fun and addicting. Anytime you contemplate buying fictional armor/weapons on ebay, you know the game has impacted your life on a deeper level than just taking up time. 

6. Divine Divinity - Everything that Diablo 2 should have been. An excellent story with fun action that doesn't get boring. Sure there are problems with this game like the HOAKY dialogue. I mean who uses a sword and shield in a medevil time period with names like Rob, Maria, and George? just to name a few. That is probably the thing I hate the most about this game. Anyway, the story is easy to follow yet at the same time semi open ended. Nice gameplay and fun overall. 

I rated all these games because they were so fun that after 60 or 70 hours of play you still were loving it. I have completed all these games except DD and I'm in the process of doing that right now. They are fun and never got tiresome. 

Games I loved through the first 30 hours or so but got boring and i didnt complete...

Baulders's gate 1 and 2
Planescape Torment
Icewind Dale
Dungeon Seige
Neverwinter Nights

Games I have never played...

Fallout series
Arcanum
Ages of Camelot
Everquest series
Gothic[/I][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
